    <h1>Help Center</h1>
    <div class="subtitle">
        Support & Guidance for Using Pharma Stock
    </div>

    <p>
        Welcome to the <strong>Pharma Stock Help Center</strong>. This page is designed
        to guide users through the features of the system and provide solutions to
        common questions and issues while using the platform.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Getting Started</h2>
    <p>
        To begin using Pharma Stock, create an account using valid details and log in
        securely. Once logged in, you will be redirected to your dashboard where you
        can manage inventory, sales, and customer records.
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Register with accurate pharmacy details</li>
        <li>Log in using your registered email and password</li>
        <li>Access your personalized dashboard after login</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. Inventory Management</h2>
    <p>
        Inventory management is the core functionality of Pharma Stock. Users can
        add, view, and manage medicines with batch-level accuracy.
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Add medicines with batch number and expiry date</li>
        <li>Update stock quantity when new supplies arrive</li>
        <li>Monitor near-expiry and out-of-stock medicines</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Sales & Billing</h2>
    <p>
        The sales module allows fast and accurate billing during customer transactions.
        The system follows FEFO (First Expired, First Out) logic to reduce wastage.
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Select medicines by batch number</li>
        <li>Generate bills dynamically</li>
        <li>Automatic stock deduction after each sale</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Customer & Sales History</h2>
    <p>
        Pharma Stock maintains a record of all transactions for reference and analysis.
        This helps shop owners track sales performance and customer purchase history.
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>View previous sales records</li>
        <li>Track customer purchase details</li>
        <li>Use history for business analysis</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Account & Security</h2>
    <p>
        User account security is a priority. Users are advised to keep their login
        credentials confidential and log out from shared devices.
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Do not share your password with others</li>
        <li>Log out after using the system on public devices</li>
        <li>Contact support in case of suspicious activity</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Common Issues & Solutions</h2>
    <div class="note">
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Unable to log in:</strong> Check your email and password and ensure Caps Lock is off.</li>
            <li><strong>Stock not updating:</strong> Refresh the page and verify entered quantities.</li>
            <li><strong>Page not accessible:</strong> Your session may have expired. Please log in again.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

